Local DJ Black Coffee announced on Wednesday that he would be speaking at the International Music Summit (IMS) set to take place in Ibiza from 23 to 25 May. According to the IMS site , the summit is a "comprehensive three-day event featuring live seminars and debates amongst the leaders of the international music community." Black Coffee made the announcement on Twitter, writing: "Honoured to be speaking at #IMSIbiza this year alongside my team!" Read his tweet here: Honored to be speaking at #IMSIbiza this year alongside my team! ????????https://t.co/dQMkaUk2g5 pic.twitter.com/Xa25IsvxyP-- #PIECESOFME (@RealBlackCoffee) February 28, 2018 Source: The Juice